ECO-ANXIETY.

Eco anxiety is basically a fear of ecological disaster. It is largely based on the current trend of announcements revolving around the plight of the environment and the Earth.

Anxiety over environmental issues may originate from a growing knowledge of the possibility of catastrophic weather occurrences, loss of livelihood or home, concerns about future generations, and emotions of hopelessness.

Some common symptoms of Eco Anxiety include: Chronic or severe stress can enhance the risk of a variety of serious health concerns. This involves heart disease, hypertension, and depression.

People suffering from eco-anxiety may also experience general anxiety symptoms.

Although resolving environmental concerns requires social change, government involvement, and companies accepting responsibility for their contributions to climate change, people can typically manage their own reactions to environmental challenges (Eco Anxiety) using a variety of methods like increasing awareness, focusing on resiliency, improving connection with nature, or even seeking medical help if necessary.

We had the opportunity to address the 6th Digital Transformation Conclave organised by @ficci_india and @stpiindia on leveraging a digital leap for socio economic transformation. 

The Disposal Company thrives on data, customer education and awareness, cutting across the unorganized market segments and spectrum of stakeholders, right from waste aggregators/ragpickers, to consumers, to brands & corporates. Our founder @bhagyashree.bhansali talked  about the stories of change that we’ve encountered along our journey and specially the ones that have left a mark on us. 
We can proudly claim that our work breaks barriers. We bridge impact, businesses, and people, across borders and identities. This growing coalition of brands, impact projects, and consumers are driving change around the world, everyday!

As we entered the decisive decade for climate action, we had sworn to bring the change we hope to see in the world. With this in mind and the belief to get a better future rolling, our founder @bhagyashree.bhansali successfully started leading the journey for The Disposal Company where we facilitate planet to profit to people movement of sustainability. 

Recently, we participated in the Digital Rajasthan Conclave’s 6th edition where not only useful insights were shared by @ficci_india and @stpiindia, but also a holistic business understanding was developed for new age entrepreneurs. Bhagyashree gave valuable inputs and her knowledge in the field of waste management also led us get a grip about how digital transformation in supply chains is leading businesses to operate on global standards of sustainability.
